The paper focuses on visualizing and understanding deep networks in computer vision, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel approach for optimizing heatmaps using integrated gradients, which involves machine learning techniques and optimization algorithms, indicating that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed approach on several benchmark datasets, which suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) may also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the importance of providing faithful explanations for deep networks, which suggests that cs.CL (Computation and Language) may be a less likely but still possible sub-category.
